SIMPLE: flexible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flexible
<hw>Flex"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>flexibilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>flexible</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being flexed or bent; admitting of being turned, bowed,
or twisted, without breaking; pliable; yielding to pressure; not stiff
or brittle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the splitting wind⟦br⟧
Makes <qex>flexible</qex> the knees of knotted oaks.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Willing or ready to yield to the influence of
others; not invincibly rigid or obstinate; tractable; manageable;
ductile; easy and compliant; wavering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Phocion was a man of great severity, and no ways
<qex>flexible</qex> to the will of the people.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Women are soft, mild, pitiful, and <qex>flexible</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Capable or being adapted or molded; plastic,;
<as>as, a <ex>flexible</ex> language</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This was a principle more <qex>flexible</qex> to their
purpose.</q> <rj><qau>Rogers.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Pliant; pliable; supple; tractable; manageable;
ductile; obsequious; inconstant; wavering.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Flex"i*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Flex"i*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flexicostate</ent>⟦br⟧
